MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: SITE IS LOCATED ON THE GIANT FOREST CA 7.5 MINUTE SERIES (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE. SITE IS LOCATED ON CHAMISE CREEK APPROXIMATELY .5 MILE UPSTREAM OF ITS CONFLUENCE WITH KAWEAH RIVER. IT IS CONSIDERED A LOW ELEVATION (750 M) CHAPARRAL FOOTHILL SITE DOMINATED BY CHAMISE (ADENOSTOMA FASCICULATUM). PRECIPITATION AVERAGES 66 CM ANNUALLY NEARLY ALL FALLING AS RAIN DURING THE WINTER MONTHS. PRIMARY SOIL SUBGROUPS INCLUDE TYPIC EXROCHREPTS  ENTIC ULTIC HAPLOXEROLLS  ULTIC HAPLOXERALFS AND ULTIC PALEXERALFS. CHAMISE CREEK IS AN INTERMITTENT FIRST ORDER TRIBUTARY GAUGED WITH AN HTYPE FLUME AND INSTRUMENTED WITH A STEVENS TYPE F WATER LEVEL RECORDER. THE CREEK IS SAMPLED OPPORTUNISTICALLY. IT IS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF LISA HAMMETT AT NATIONAL BIOLOGICAL SERVICE FIELD STATION  SEQUOIAKINGS CANYON NATIONAL PARK THREE RIVERS CALIFORNIA 93271 PH.(209)5653123. MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: SITE IS AT THE OUTFLOW OF EMERALD LAKE FOUND ON THE LODGEPOLE CA 7.5 MINUTE SERIES (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE. IT IS A SUBALPINE (3000 M) CIRQUE LARGELY TREELESS BUT INCLUDING LODGEPOLE PINE (PINUS CONTORTA) WESTERN WHITE PINE(PINUS MONTICOLA) FOXTAIL PINE (PINUS BALFOURIANA) AND RED FIR(ABIES MAGNIFICA). ANNUAL PRECIP HAS VARIED FROM 70 TO 300 CM IN THE PAST DECADE NEARLY ALL AS WINTER SNOW. TWENTY PERCENT OF THE BASIN HAS DEVELOPED SOIL WHICH INCLUDES LITHIC CRYMBREPTS AND CRYAQUEPTS. OUTFLOW IS GAUGED WITH A MODIFIED VNOTCH WEIR THERMISTOR AND PRESSURE TRANSDUCER. AN AEROCHEM METRICS SAMPLER AND METEOROLOGICAL STATION LOCATED AT THE LAKE INFLOW PROVIDE PRECIP AND WEATHER DATA FOR THE CATCHMENT. IT IS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE LISA HAMMETT AT THE NBS FIELD STATION  SEQUOIAKINGS CANYON NATIONAL PARK THREE RIVERS CALIFORNIA 93271 PH.(209)5653123.
